  "prompt": "What did George Lucas think of the Force Awakens?",
  "response": "George Lucas has been somewhat critical of \"The Force Awakens.\" In a 2015 interview with Charlie Rose, he suggested that the film was too derivative of the original Star Wars and followed a safe, familiar path. He compared it to selling a \"Ferrari without an engine\" and felt that Disney was more interested in making a marketable film than telling an original story. However, he didn't outright condemn the movie and acknowledged that filmmaking is a business. Despite his reservations, he sold Lucasfilm to Disney in 2012, which gave them creative control over the new Star Wars films.",
